After Action Review (AAR)
Subject: Lynis Security Hardening Session – Fedora 44 (N100 Laptop)
Date: 26 June 2026
Hostname: tufundun-l10
1. Objective
Improve the system’s security posture as measured by Lynis.
2. Initial State

Hardening Index: 70
Several weak kernel parameters, umask, password aging, etc.

3. Actions Taken & Commands Used
Kernel Hardening:
Bashsudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/99-hardening.conf << EOF
fs.protected_fifos = 2
fs.protected_regular = 2
kernel.kptr_restrict = 2
kernel.modules_disabled = 1
kernel.sysrq = 0
kernel.unprivileged_bpf_disabled = 1
kernel.yama.ptrace_scope = 2
net.core.bpf_jit_harden = 2
net.ipv4.conf.all.log_martians = 1
net.ipv4.conf.default.log_martians = 1
net.ipv4.conf.all.rp_filter = 1
EOF

sudo sysctl --system
Password Policy:
Bashsudo sed -i 's/^PASS_MAX_DAYS.*/PASS_MAX_DAYS   90/' /etc/login.defs
sudo sed -i 's/^PASS_MIN_DAYS.*/PASS_MIN_DAYS   1/' /etc/login.defs
sudo sed -i 's/^PASS_WARN_AGE.*/PASS_WARN_AGE   7/' /etc/login.defs
Umask Improvement:
Bashsudo bash -c 'echo "umask 027" >> /etc/profile.d/umask.sh'
Hosts File Cleanup:
Bashsudo cp /etc/hosts /etc/hosts.bak
sudo awk '!seen[$0]++' /etc/hosts | sudo tee /etc/hosts
Login Banners:
Bashecho "Authorized access only. All activity is logged." | sudo tee /etc/issue /etc/issue.net
